244
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:34,368
A dad's just a concept to him,
not a person.

245
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:35,995
But Astor --

246
00:16:37,079 --> 00:16:39,165
she remembers what
he put us through.

247
00:16:42,877 --> 00:16:44,879
Well, at least you're
not married anymore.

248
00:16:46,464 --> 00:16:47,798
That's just it.

249
00:16:48,591 --> 00:16:50,092
Technically, we are.

250
00:16:51,469 --> 00:16:53,971
When Paul went to prison,
I started divorce proceedings,

251
00:16:53,971 --> 00:16:56,265
but he refused to
sign the paperwork.

252
00:16:56,974 --> 00:16:58,392
As a power play?

253
00:16:59,477 --> 00:17:00,686
I don't think so.

254
00:17:00,978 --> 00:17:03,564
I think for all the
darkness that haunts him,

255
00:17:03,564 --> 00:17:05,566
Paul loves having a family.

256
00:17:06,776 --> 00:17:08,277
I think he's just
afraid to let go.

257
00:17:10,780 --> 00:17:12,281
When did you first notice it?

258
00:17:13,991 --> 00:17:16,661
This darkness inside
the guy you fell for.

259
00:17:19,664 --> 00:17:21,290
I always knew it was there.

260
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:24,085
I guess I just didn't
think I deserved better...

261
00:17:25,795 --> 00:17:26,796
Till I met you.

262
00:17:36,264 --> 00:17:37,765
I have a dark side, too.

263
00:17:41,185 --> 00:17:42,270
What? I do.

264
00:17:43,271 --> 00:17:45,064
Somehow I doubt that.

265
00:17:45,982 --> 00:17:47,984
You have a good heart, Dexter.

266
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:50,861
You're not like Paul.
You don't hurt people.

267
00:17:56,659 --> 00:17:57,994
Innocent people.

268
00:18:03,958 --> 00:18:05,793
I don't hurt innocent people.

269
00:18:29,859 --> 00:18:32,778
Hey, dude,
the bowling alley's around the corner.

270
00:18:36,365 --> 00:18:38,993
Hey, I'm looking
for Jeremy Downs.

271
00:18:38,993 --> 00:18:43,080
Jeremy? He vacated
the premises.

272
00:18:44,290 --> 00:18:47,585
Focus. I'm trying
to find Jeremy.

273
00:18:48,669 --> 00:18:50,087
Oh, I get it.

274
00:18:53,466 --> 00:18:54,383
Look, man,

275
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:57,178
I'm not really into
that homo shit,

276
00:18:57,261 --> 00:19:00,264
but I'm kind of short
on money for weed,

277
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:03,476
so I guess I'll do it for
less than Jeremy's charging.

278
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:07,271
- Wait. What does Jeremy charge?
- Jeremy's selling himself?

279
00:19:07,772 --> 00:19:11,776
He's always hanging out with the
brokeback boys down at Flamingo Park.

280
00:19:11,859 --> 00:19:14,278
Comes back with
fistfuls of cash.

281
00:19:22,662 --> 00:19:25,164
It's me.
Get your ass over to Neil Perry's place.

282
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:27,875
- You're gonna want to see this.
- Deb, it's my day off.

283
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:29,293
Just get your ass over here.

284
00:19:29,293 --> 00:19:31,587
We're about to bust open the
goods on the ice-truck killer.

285
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:47,186
Not what I expected.

286
00:20:23,389 --> 00:20:24,765
So lifelike.

287
00:20:37,194 --> 00:20:39,864
Hey, Dex.
I thought you'd want to be here.

288
00:20:40,281 --> 00:20:42,575
Something's buried down there.
Masuka's been digging all night.

289
00:20:42,575 --> 00:20:43,868
I hate to break
this to you, Deb,

290
00:20:43,868 --> 00:20:45,786
but you know you've got
the wrong guy here, right?

291
00:20:46,787 --> 00:20:49,081
The ice-truck killer drains
the blood from his victims,

292
00:20:49,081 --> 00:20:51,876
freezes their bodies,
and only then severs their limbs.

293
00:20:51,876 --> 00:20:54,962
It's clean and efficient --
his psychological signature.

294
00:20:55,087 --> 00:20:57,381
Neil Perry, on the other hand,
stuffs roadkill.

295
00:20:57,381 --> 00:20:59,175
Yeah, and turns it into
fucked-up fantasy shit.

296
00:20:59,175 --> 00:21:01,760
But the fantasies are all wrong.
The guy we're looking for

297
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:04,472
wouldn't turn dead,
dirty things into living cartoons.

298
00:21:04,472 --> 00:21:06,599
- He'd find that pathetic.
- How do you know?

299
00:21:07,475 --> 00:21:09,268
Because it is pathetic.

300
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:12,688
Deb, trust me.
Neil Perry is not a killer.

301
00:21:12,688 --> 00:21:14,565
He's a dabbler.
He's a waste of time.

302
00:21:14,690 --> 00:21:17,359
If the guy we're looking for took
his early fantasies out on animals,

303
00:21:17,359 --> 00:21:18,861
he'd bury them,
not display them.

304
00:21:18,861 --> 00:21:22,281
And want about an early human kill?
Would he bury that, too?

305
00:21:22,865 --> 00:21:24,867
- Sure. Probably.
- Then turn around.

306
00:21:25,785 --> 00:21:27,077
You were saying?

307
00:21:28,996 --> 00:21:30,372
It looks like an adult female.

308
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:33,876
Any idea how long the
body's been down there?

309
00:21:34,168 --> 00:21:35,586
Based on decomposition,

310
00:21:35,586 --> 00:21:37,963
she's been tits up for two,
maybe three years.

311
00:21:37,963 --> 00:21:39,798
We'll know more
after the autopsy.

312
00:21:39,882 --> 00:21:42,176
What happened to the limbs?
Did they rot off?

313
00:21:43,093 --> 00:21:45,971
No. They're clean cuts.

314
00:21:46,096 --> 00:21:47,973
But he didn't chop
up the whole body.

315
00:21:48,682 --> 00:21:50,559
This could be
Perry's first kill,

316
00:21:50,768 --> 00:21:52,561
like he was experimenting.

317
00:21:53,395 --> 00:21:55,272
You're the expert, Dex.
What do you think?

318
00:21:57,566 --> 00:21:58,984
Sure. Sounds good.

319
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:01,987
Actually, it sounds
perfectly awful.

320
00:22:03,072 --> 00:22:06,784
For weeks, I've felt like a
student in a master class.

321
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:09,495
Is it really possible that
the master's on the run?

322
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:12,373
And even more tragic,

323
00:22:12,581 --> 00:22:14,375
does he live in a double-wide?

324
00:22:16,377 --> 00:22:18,879
The gravitron goes
so fast, mom.

325
00:22:18,963 --> 00:22:22,091
My dad took me on
it three times.

326
00:22:22,091 --> 00:22:23,384
Wow. Is that so?

327
00:22:25,261 --> 00:22:27,972
All right,
let me cut you guys up some fruit.

328
00:22:28,097 --> 00:22:30,683
Astor wouldn't go.
She was afraid.

329
00:22:30,891 --> 00:22:33,769
So what?
I don't like fast rides.

330
00:22:34,895 --> 00:22:35,688
Shh!

331
00:22:38,566 --> 00:22:40,192
Hello?

332
00:22:42,862 --> 00:22:45,364
- Who wants doughnuts?
- I do.

333
00:22:45,364 --> 00:22:47,283
Paul, you can't just walk
in here whenever you want.

334
00:22:47,283 --> 00:22:48,659
You don't live here anymore.

335
00:22:49,785 --> 00:22:52,663
Oh. Sorry about that.
Old habits.

336
00:22:52,788 --> 00:22:54,498
I'll ring the
doorbell next time.

337
00:22:58,794 --> 00:23:00,588
I got these for you.

338
00:23:03,883 --> 00:23:08,596
All right.
I'll just put them in, uh, something.

339
00:23:08,762 --> 00:23:10,598
Dad, can I have a doughnut?

340
00:23:10,681 --> 00:23:12,266
You got it, buddy. Coming up.

341
00:23:12,474 --> 00:23:14,476
What, now you're making
me out to be the bad guy?

342
00:23:14,476 --> 00:23:16,186
They haven't had breakfast yet.

343
00:23:17,688 --> 00:23:20,858
You know what? Kidlet, my bad.
Sorry about that.

344
00:23:20,983 --> 00:23:23,193
These doughnuts are
for after school.

345
00:23:23,193 --> 00:23:25,779
But I could whip up
some eggs and pancakes.

346
00:23:25,779 --> 00:23:28,657
- Paul!
- Very little syrup, I promise.

347
00:23:28,657 --> 00:23:29,992
And meat

348
00:23:29,992 --> 00:23:31,076
You into neat?
- Uh-huh.

349
00:23:31,076 --> 00:23:32,369
I like meat

350
00:23:32,995 --> 00:23:36,665
I like meat on my feet.
It's real squishy.

351
00:23:36,665 --> 00:23:41,086
Paul. You can't do
this anymore, Paul.

352
00:23:41,086 --> 00:23:44,673
What?! What?!
Help raise my kids?!

353
00:23:45,090 --> 00:23:47,885
Yes, I can. That's my job.

354
00:23:50,763 --> 00:23:51,972
All right, look.

355
00:23:54,183 --> 00:23:57,895
I can't even begin to understand
how difficult this has been for you,

356
00:23:57,895 --> 00:24:00,064
Rita, being a single mom, okay?

357
00:24:01,857 --> 00:24:05,361
And for that,
I'm eternally sorry.

358
00:24:06,987 --> 00:24:08,197
I let you down.

359
00:24:10,282 --> 00:24:11,784
I let everybody down.

360
00:24:16,997 --> 00:24:19,667
But if I could just
find that frying pan.

361
00:24:19,959 --> 00:24:23,587
Astor... want to help
me find the frying pan?

362
00:24:31,470 --> 00:24:33,764
We got a profile of Neil Perry.

363
00:24:33,889 --> 00:24:35,391
He's a computer expert.

364
00:24:35,557 --> 00:24:38,477
I.Q. off the chart.
He's a loner, no pryors.

365
00:24:38,686 --> 00:24:40,479
His father split when he was 6.

366
00:24:40,688 --> 00:24:44,775
His mother was an alcoholic, abusive,
and possibly his first victim.

367
00:24:45,484 --> 00:24:46,986
Roberta Perry.

368
00:24:47,277 --> 00:24:49,989
Dental records say she was
the one under the patio.

369
00:24:50,072 --> 00:24:51,573
Now, Neil kept her death quiet

370
00:24:51,657 --> 00:24:54,868
by cashing her social-security
checks for the last two years,

371
00:24:54,868 --> 00:24:57,079
but he did not kill her
for the money.

372
00:24:57,788 --> 00:24:58,580
Morgan?

373
00:24:59,081 --> 00:25:00,457
We think he wanted release.

374
00:25:00,582 --> 00:25:02,584
Roberta Perry ran
her son's life,

375
00:25:02,793 --> 00:25:04,586
controlled him,
beat him as a kid.

376
00:25:04,670 --> 00:25:06,588
We think he dreamt about
killing her for years.

377
00:25:06,672 --> 00:25:08,465
I just spoke with Perry's
cellphone provider.

378
00:25:08,590 --> 00:25:09,967
Can they track his location?

379
00:25:10,175 --> 00:25:11,969
No signal --
he probably turned off his phone.

380
00:25:11,969 --> 00:25:14,179
But, according to records,
he used it

381
00:25:14,263 --> 00:25:17,057
on some of the nights the ice-truck
killer victims were taken.

382
00:25:17,057 --> 00:25:18,183
Who did he call?

383
00:25:18,392 --> 00:25:20,185
Voice mail, mostly,
checking messages.

384
00:25:20,269 --> 00:25:21,979
Verizon triangulated
the location.

385
00:25:22,062 --> 00:25:23,897
All the calls came
from the same place --

386
00:25:23,897 --> 00:25:26,191
a six-block area on
southwest 8th street.

387
00:25:26,191 --> 00:25:29,361
The Tamiami trail.
That strip's full of no-tell motels.

388
00:25:29,361 --> 00:25:31,363
It's like a happy hunting
ground for hookers.

389
00:25:31,363 --> 00:25:34,074
There's a good chance that's
where he's killing his victims.

390
00:25:34,074 --> 00:25:36,368
Let's recanvass
the area for leads.

391
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:38,078
Now that we've got
a photo of this guy,

392
00:25:38,078 --> 00:25:40,164
maybe we can find somebody
who actually saw him.

393
00:25:40,664 --> 00:25:41,582
Let's go.

394
00:25:43,167 --> 00:25:45,085
You're starting
to look like her.

395
00:25:45,669 --> 00:25:47,963
Want to stop by your house,
check in with your family?

396
00:25:47,963 --> 00:25:49,798
I'd rather check in
with your brother.

397
00:25:49,798 --> 00:25:52,092
His instincts are usually
pretty good on this stuff.

398
00:25:52,092 --> 00:25:54,261
Yeah, not today.
He'd just piss on our parade.

399
00:25:54,261 --> 00:25:56,096
He needs his day off.

400
00:25:57,473 --> 00:25:59,266
The first time I saw his work,

401
00:25:59,475 --> 00:26:03,395
I felt like a spanish explorer landing
of the shores of the new world.

402
00:26:03,896 --> 00:26:07,858
No blood in the victims,
no spatter, no stain.

403
00:26:09,276 --> 00:26:11,361
Deb is wrong about him.

404
00:26:11,987 --> 00:26:14,782
It's okay.
Hell, I've made mistakes.

405
00:26:15,074 --> 00:26:18,285
In fact, I'm about to
correct a big one right now.

406
00:26:20,078 --> 00:26:21,872
Jeremy Downs.

407
00:26:24,291 --> 00:26:25,959
Hey, you want company?

408
00:26:26,168 --> 00:26:28,295
Just keep walking
and looking ahead.

409
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:32,758
There's some mangroves over by the lake.
We can go in there.

410
00:26:32,758 --> 00:26:35,469
It's too public.
My car's in the parking lot.

411
00:26:35,886 --> 00:26:38,972
- Are your windows tinted?
- I said, "eyes front."

412
00:26:41,975 --> 00:26:43,477
What's wrong?

413
00:26:48,357 --> 00:26:50,067
Shit. Shit.

414
00:26:50,692 --> 00:26:52,486
Get the fuck out of my way!

415
00:26:53,487 --> 00:26:55,989
Take it easy, Jeremy!
Stay right there!

416
00:26:56,198 --> 00:26:58,575
Take him down! Take him down!

417
00:27:00,077 --> 00:27:03,288
Hands behind your back.
Stand up! Stand up!

418
00:27:16,885 --> 00:27:19,263
Miami Metro P.D.
Can we have a minute?

419
00:27:19,471 --> 00:27:19,763
Yeah.

420
00:27:20,097 --> 00:27:22,766
- This guy look familiar?
- I don't know.

421
00:27:23,058 --> 00:27:24,393
They come. They go.

422
00:27:24,685 --> 00:27:27,187
You get it? They "come."

423
00:27:27,688 --> 00:27:30,190
Look, my feet are aching
from pounding the pavement.

424
00:27:30,190 --> 00:27:31,859
You think you
could help us out?

425
00:27:32,192 --> 00:27:33,068
- What's your name?

426
00:27:34,069 --> 00:27:36,488
Laline Consuelo Garci? G?mez.

427
00:27:40,367 --> 00:27:41,160
Laline...

428
00:27:42,369 --> 00:27:44,997
O?ste del hombre que
le dicen el ice-truck killer?

429
00:27:45,289 --> 00:27:47,165
- S?.
- Puede ser el.

430
00:27:47,666 --> 00:27:51,461
So let's try this again.
Have you seen this man?

431
00:27:54,173 --> 00:27:57,384
He's a regular.
Rents a room by the month -- cash.

432
00:27:57,384 --> 00:27:58,468
When was the last
time he was here?

433
00:27:58,468 --> 00:28:01,263
He's here now. He brought a
girl to his room this morning.

434
00:28:01,263 --> 00:28:02,890
A working girl? A hooker?

435
00:28:03,473 --> 00:28:06,476
- What's the room number?
- 20. Here's the master.

436
00:28:06,685 --> 00:28:09,271
Call for backup.
Let's hope this girl is still alive.

437
00:28:10,272 --> 00:28:13,567
- Do we wait for tactical?
- Not with a possible victim in there.

438
00:28:28,874 --> 00:28:29,791
Clear.

439
00:28:30,459 --> 00:28:33,295
It's okay. We're here now.
You're safe.

440
00:28:36,298 --> 00:28:39,968
Please get me out -- hurry --
before he comes back!

441
00:28:40,177 --> 00:28:42,095
- Where is he?
- Please, I want to get out!

442
00:28:42,179 --> 00:28:43,180
Where was he going?

443
00:28:43,180 --> 00:28:45,891
The liquor store.
He said he's coming right back.

444
00:28:49,561 --> 00:28:50,687
What?

445
00:28:55,067 --> 00:28:56,777
Hey, where's Doakes?
He paged me.

446
00:28:56,777 --> 00:28:58,570
We need your report from
that kid in the alley.

447
00:28:58,987 --> 00:29:00,280
But it's my day off.

448
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:02,866
I was just at Don Shula's
famous golf course.

449
00:29:02,991 --> 00:29:06,662
- Did you finish your report or not?
- Yeah, it's in my lab.

450
00:29:06,870 --> 00:29:09,581
Wait. I'm on to you.

451
00:29:12,584 --> 00:29:13,877
Excuse me?

452
00:29:14,086 --> 00:29:16,797
Your crazy-ass,
knife-slashing two-step in the alley.

453
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:17,881
You were right.

454
00:29:18,090 --> 00:29:20,759
You said the killer had
previous experience. He did.

455
00:29:21,677 --> 00:29:23,971
Oh. Really?

456
00:29:23,971 --> 00:29:26,974
Masuka lifted a print from the
alley that matched a kid from juvie.

457
00:29:27,474 --> 00:29:30,269
Cut up a victim five years ago.
Same knife technique.

458
00:29:30,978 --> 00:29:33,188
We just grabbed him
at Flamingo Park.

459
00:29:33,897 --> 00:29:35,190
Great work, sergeant.

460
00:29:35,190 --> 00:29:37,276
Yeah. Your instincts
were dead-on.

461
00:29:37,859 --> 00:29:40,279
They're always dead-on when it
comes to killers. Why is that?

462
00:29:42,698 --> 00:29:44,157
I'll just go get that report.

463
00:29:44,866 --> 00:29:46,368
I'm watching you.

464
00:30:00,882 --> 00:30:01,967
Miss me?

465
00:30:02,175 --> 00:30:05,387
Police. On the ground.
Get down slowly.

466
00:30:10,183 --> 00:30:12,769
Now the day is over

467
00:30:12,978 --> 00:30:15,272
Night is drawing nigh

468
00:30:15,272 --> 00:30:16,189
Get down!

469
00:30:16,273 --> 00:30:21,987
The shadows of the evening
steal across the sky

470
00:30:21,987 --> 00:30:26,074
- I said get the fuck down!
- Now the darkness gathers

471
00:30:26,074 --> 00:30:29,661
- Facedown -- let's go!
- Stars begin to peep

472
00:30:29,870 --> 00:30:33,790
birds and beasts and
flowers

473
00:30:33,790 --> 00:30:37,377
soon will be asleep

474
00:30:40,964 --> 00:30:43,467
What else do you want to
put in the concoction?

475
00:30:43,675 --> 00:30:45,677
Gummi bears.

476
00:30:45,677 --> 00:30:48,472
How do you two plan to eat that,
spread it on toast?

477
00:30:48,680 --> 00:30:50,682
It already has toast in it.

478
00:30:51,475 --> 00:30:53,268
So it does.

479
00:30:54,895 --> 00:30:56,563
Keep mashing.
I'll get the door.

480
00:31:00,859 --> 00:31:03,195
Oh. Hey, there, big guy.

481
00:31:03,278 --> 00:31:06,198
Uh, Dexter, right?

482
00:31:06,365 --> 00:31:08,283
Paul, hi. Rita's not here.

483
00:31:08,492 --> 00:31:11,161
Oh, that's okay.
I'm actually here for the kids.

484
00:31:11,369 --> 00:31:14,081
I came to dazzle
them with my booty.

485
00:31:14,289 --> 00:31:16,583
This booty.

486
00:31:18,168 --> 00:31:21,379
This is awkward.
I'm afraid I'm not comfortable

487
00:31:21,379 --> 00:31:23,298
letting you inside the
house without Rita here.

488
00:31:25,175 --> 00:31:27,969
Who are you, anyway,
like, the babysitter?

489
00:31:28,095 --> 00:31:29,888
I'm watching the
kids right now,

490
