00:47:34,477 --> 00:47:36,187
Things have changed.

742
00:47:38,981 --> 00:47:40,858
Everything has changed.

743
00:47:44,195 --> 00:47:48,282
I always prided myself on
being an outsider, but now...

744
00:47:51,660 --> 00:47:54,580
I feel the need to
connect with someone.

745
00:48:00,086 --> 00:48:01,796
I saw myself in Jeremy...

746
00:48:03,297 --> 00:48:05,466
But instead of helping
him like Harry helped me,

747
00:48:05,466 --> 00:48:09,178
I gave him a piece of fortune-cookie
advice that he never even heard.

748
00:48:10,096 --> 00:48:11,097
I failed him.

749
00:48:12,890 --> 00:48:14,475
He deserves better...

750
00:48:15,768 --> 00:48:17,561
And he'll get it from now on.

751
00:48:41,293 --> 00:48:42,962
I guess I was wrong.

752
00:48:44,964 --> 00:48:47,383
Jeremy did hear my advice.

753
00:48:48,968 --> 00:48:51,470
He killed someone
who deserved to die.

754
00:48:53,889 --> 00:48:55,558
What's the status on Perry?

755
00:48:55,891 --> 00:48:57,268
I'm having him
transferred right now.

756
00:48:57,268 --> 00:48:59,979
The D.A. wants to keep him at county,
pending arraignment.

757
00:49:02,273 --> 00:49:03,566
Maria,

758
00:49:03,983 --> 00:49:07,778
it was your decision making that
led to his capture and arrest,

759
00:49:08,487 --> 00:49:12,992
and you made all our lives easier
by getting the bastard to confess.

760
00:49:12,992 --> 00:49:14,160
I'm just doing my job.

761
00:49:14,869 --> 00:49:17,788
It feels good to be
praising your police work

762
00:49:17,788 --> 00:49:19,665
instead of your
politics for a change.

763
00:49:22,460 --> 00:49:24,170
We need to make an
official comment.

764
00:49:24,170 --> 00:49:25,963
Don't worry.
I'll keep it short.

765
00:49:26,589 --> 00:49:28,757
I'm just heading downstairs
now for the press conference.

766
00:49:28,757 --> 00:49:30,092
The press conference is over.

767
00:49:30,968 --> 00:49:34,471
Oh, and, uh, don't worry.
I kept it short.

768
00:49:36,056 --> 00:49:38,058
You got to be
fucking kidding me.

769
00:49:38,184 --> 00:49:41,187
- That was my bust.
- This is my department.

770
00:49:44,356 --> 00:49:46,984
Did you at least
give me credit?

771
00:49:47,276 --> 00:49:50,779
Yes. I just gave it to you.
Haven't you been listening?

772
00:49:58,996 --> 00:50:01,457
Ever since Harry's death,
I've been alone...

773
00:50:05,169 --> 00:50:08,088
...but now,
for the first time...

774
00:50:09,882 --> 00:50:11,091
I feel alone.

775
00:50:11,675 --> 00:50:13,385
How long you need
with the prisoner?

776
00:50:18,557 --> 00:50:20,392
As long as I can get.

777
00:50:20,976 --> 00:50:24,271
Jeremy is gone,
and Neil Perry will soon vanish

778
00:50:24,271 --> 00:50:26,273
into the catacombs
of the system.

779
00:50:26,982 --> 00:50:29,276
I have so many
questions for him.

780
00:50:30,486 --> 00:50:32,988
How did he discover my secrets?

781
00:50:33,572 --> 00:50:35,658
What was his message to me?

782
00:50:37,993 --> 00:50:41,664
He's been in my home,
my photos...

783
00:50:42,957 --> 00:50:44,166
my life.

784
00:50:45,084 --> 00:50:46,460
He knows me.

785
00:50:47,962 --> 00:50:49,880
Now I need to know him...

786
00:50:56,595 --> 00:50:59,265
...to connect face-to-face

787
00:51:00,474 --> 00:51:03,060
before he's beyond
my reach forever.

788
00:51:15,489 --> 00:51:16,490
Hi.

789
00:51:19,994 --> 00:51:21,787
Who the fuck are you?

